In this article, President Trump addresses allegations made by a magazine regarding his remarks about the military and fallen heroes. He denies making any negative statements and calls the allegations fake news. He also expresses his disagreement with John McCain but emphasizes that he respected him and approved his funeral arrangements. Trump explains that he was unable to attend a ceremony in France due to bad weather and security concerns. He criticizes the magazine for publishing false information and accuses them of trying to influence the upcoming presidential election. Trump concludes by denouncing the fake press and thanking those in attendance.